inference: Final Answer: \\boxed{50\pi}. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: The radius of the base of the cone is $10/2 = 5$, so the volume of the cone is \[\frac{1}{3} \pi \cdot 5^2 \cdot 6 = \boxed{50 \pi}.\]
